The paper discusses the development of tools for wrapper maintenance, which involves extracting data from Web sources. This topic is closely related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB), as well as machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) since the algorithm learns structural information about data from positive examples alone.
